## 3. Clean Core Scorecard

The Clean Core Score measures the ratio of modern/released API usage vs. deprecated patterns.

```
Clean Core Score = Clean Patterns / (Clean + Deprecated Patterns) × 100
                 = {{ clean_count }} / ({{ clean_count }} + {{ deprecated_count }}) × 100
                 = {{ clean_core_score }}%
```

### SAP Clean Core Dimensions

| Dimension | Description | Status |
|-----------|-------------|--------|
| **Extensions** | BAdIs, Key User extensibility vs. modifications | {{ ext_status | default('Review') }} |
| **Integrations** | Released APIs, CPI/Event Mesh vs. direct RFC | {{ int_status | default('Review') }} |
| **Data** | CDS views vs. direct table access | {{ data_status | default('Review') }} |
| **Processes** | Standard workflows vs. custom | {{ proc_status | default('Review') }} |
| **Operations** | Standard monitoring, ALM integration | {{ ops_status | default('Review') }} |

