## 11. Recommendations & Remediation Plan

### Priority Actions

| # | Action | Priority | Impact | Effort |
|---|--------|----------|--------|--------|
{% for rec in recommendations %}| {{ loop.index }} | {{ rec.action }} | {{ rec.priority }} | {{ rec.impact }} | {{ rec.effort }} |
{% endfor %}
{% if not recommendations %}| 1 | Replace direct standard table writes with released APIs | High | High | Medium |
| 2 | Migrate SELECT on standard tables to released CDS views | Medium | Medium | High |
| 3 | Plan Fiori migration for classic Dynpro UIs | Medium | High | High |
| 4 | Add unit test coverage to critical objects | Medium | Medium | Medium |
| 5 | Review RFC destinations for CPI migration path | Low | Medium | Low |
{% endif %}

### Best Practices Checklist

- [ ] All custom objects follow `Z<TOWER>_` naming convention
- [ ] No direct access to standard SAP internal tables
- [ ] Released APIs used for all SAP standard functionality
- [ ] BAdIs used instead of classic modifications (SMOD/CMOD)
- [ ] CDS views used instead of SE11 views
- [ ] Exception classes used for error handling (not `sy-subrc`)
- [ ] Unit tests present for business-critical logic
- [ ] No native SQL or dynamic code generation
- [ ] RFC destinations documented and planned for CPI migration
- [ ] Fiori apps planned for user-facing screens

